arts.ttl: Omar Marmoush masterclass propels Eintracht Frankfurt to thrilling 4-2 victory over resilient Holstein Kiel
arts.sum: Omar Marmoush scored twice and assisted twice as Eintracht Frankfurt defeated Holstein Kiel 4-2 in a thrilling Bundesliga encounter, maintaining their strong start to the season. In the 25th minute, the deadlock was broken with Omar Marmoush receiving the ball on the left flank, dribbling past several Kiel defenders, and unleashing a left-footed shot that beat the keeper at the near post.

arts.ttl: Marmoush carries Frankfurt past Kiel with two goals and two assists
arts.sum: In a high-octane affair at the Holstein-Stadion on Sunday afternoon, Eintracht Frankfurt were able to extend their league winning streak to four straight Bundesliga matches with a 4-2 win over newly promoted Holstein Kiel. The star-of-the-show was once again none other than Frankfurt's Egyptian international Omar Marmoush, who scored two goals and set-up another pair in the victory. Marmoush's play helped the SGE overcome their hosts, who did demonstrate some offensive prowess.

arts.ttl: Holstein Kiel vs Eintracht Frankfurt preview: Visitors in strong form
arts.sum: Newcomers Holstein Kiel prepare to host Eintracht Frankfurt this weekend after collecting their first Bundesliga point last time out against Bochum.
